# CRITICAL — env file naming convention to avoid prod bundles pointing at staging:
#
#   .env.development.local  → loaded ONLY by `npm run dev` (staging Supabase)
#   .env.production         → loaded ONLY by `npm run build` (PROD Supabase, committed)
#   .env.local              → loaded by BOTH (would override .env.production at build time)
#                              ❌ DO NOT use unless you really mean it for both modes
#
# History (2026-05-20): a stale `.env.local` containing staging keys was being
# baked into `npm run build` and deployed to penghasilantambahan.com, so every
# prod user was actually talking to the staging DB. Spent ~6 turns chasing
# ghost bugs before catching it via the session-diagnostic banner (admin's
# auth.uid was a staging user id on a prod URL — dead giveaway).
#
# Copy this file → `.env.development.local` for local dev (staging Supabase).

VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-public-key
